annotation.TEXT: Ooh, and beating the boss also unlocks that world's Time Attack! (With the exception of the final world, which you unlock the Time Attack for by clearing a particular non-boss level.)

And there we go! BTW, if you don't make it, there is a one-way wall you can go through to return to the right side of the level so that you can try again, but it'll be a bit harder if you already got the mana star, since that won't respawn.
With either gate switch open, you can access this timer switch, which lets you proceed to the final leg of the level.
Alright! Defeating a boss gets you 9000 points, and a number of stars depending on what boss it is, which is 1 star in this case.
Yeah, I'm not gonna try to add that slime below to that combo. Alright, that's gems #1 and #3 collected. Now for gem #2 below...
Instead, let's head straight into world 2-1 with Daria!
I think it takes 16 clicks to break the armor this time, and then this will happen again at 60% damage and 80% damage, taking 3 more clicks to break the armor each time.
Whoops, that thin floor on the right isn't the one-way passage.
Ah, I can get through the rotating door without breaking my combo.
Heh, that rotating door near the goal is still spinning. They seem to maintain perpetual motion if nothing is obstructing them.

Alright, he's pretty small and pretty fast now. Also, he'll spit out two more regular slimes before he's finished off, so make sure to destroy them before dealing the final blow if you want the points for them.
Whoa, I'm surprised I didn't bump into the slime that had appeared just to my right there.
Alright, I'm back in the green zone for health. Now, let's be a bit more careful while comboing.
Hyper combo! (5 kills, 7500 points.)
I'm low on mana, but these coins will certainly help!
Add a space between "1" and "is" here.
And, Daria recovers 1/4 of a unit of HP with each enemy she zaps to death, which is nice.
...1 vote for Michael Phelps, 1 vote for "D'oh, I missed!", 1 vote for 8-C, and 9 votes for 1-BOSS! So, we're gonna be playing the boss level now! Mira, you ready? Of course you're ready!
Whoa, be careful not to bump into the ceiling spikes.

Now, 20 seconds is way more than enough to get through that timer gate, but there's another one at the top that the final gem is behind, so you've gotta race here. Fortunately, there's a mana star on the way that'll help you out.
Fatality.
So, guys, in addition to the usual level votes, vote for whether I should show off Time Attack next time or not!
I'm going to intentionally leave some enemy-dropped coins behind for now, to help me with getting the 3-star bonus at the end, as usual.
Awesome. Now, let's see here... The next possible coin value for the 3-star bonus is 37. I'm sure I left enough enemy-dropped coins throughout the level to be able to reach that amount.

Now, the game doesn't automatically plop you straight into the boss battle. There's an actual level to play through first to reach the boss. However, it's generally quite short, and there are no gems to worry about finding.
Easy enough. And, that's it for the enemies in this level. Now, with either gate switch pressed (it doesn't really matter which), head back to where the level started.
Oh, and world 2's blue levels cost 6 red gems to play, compared to world 1's costing 5.
Stop flying like a drunk, Daria.
Alright, I'm not gonna try to squeeze any more into that combo. Now, let's take a look at this setup here...
On top of that, he now deploys regular slime enemies as I damage him. They're easy to destroy, of course, but I want to try to get combos with them for more points.
While standing on the green switch, click on the boss repeatedly. And after I believe 13 clicks...
Oh, man. There he is. We'll be getting to the big guy in just a moment.
Stand on it or bump into it to make it rotate. Simple enough.
♦ush!
To be continued... Yo!
Alright, there is a rotating door that the level name mentioned.
Interestingly, I have exactly enough red gems to play both 8-C and 2-A next time, if the votes favor those levels...
The yellow switch lets me get out of there easily, and also grants me access to the blue switch above. However, I need to adjust these rotating doors some more before I hit the blue switch.

It's kinda too bad standing on the green switch ends up stopping my combo. Let's see if I can cleverly get a combo of more than 3 kills during the boss here, by leaving the next 3 summoned slimes alive at first...
Awesome combo! (7 kills, 14,000 points.)
Super combo! (4 kills, 5000 points.)
Oh, man. A bunch of wall slimes! Hit these gate switches to release them so that you can slay them!
Yep, his green armor is no more... for now. Also, he shrunk in size a little bit, and is now moving slightly faster.
Take advantage of the rotating doors' inertia to help you out.
Now, with Time Attack unlocked, I can go back to any of the levels in that world that I've already cleared, and click on the clock button to Time Attack it, but I'm not gonna do that right now.

Alright, so let's start off by shooting the boss to deal damage to him, which makes sense, of course. Also, there's a health potion in the upper-right corner of the room, in case you need it. But, what about that green switch?
Okay, how do I want to combo these slimes? Hmm...
Irvette, your turn!
Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! Okay, here are the voting results: 1 vote for me to say "All right, it's boss time, Mr. Guy Man!", 1 vote for a regularly scheduled magical frog...
Oh, what's this? After removing 20% of the boss's life, he turned green, and I can no longer harm him with my bullets. This is when the green switch comes into play.
Awesome. Now I'll remove his armor (by clicking on him 19 times while standing on the switch), and then start killing the little slimes for a greater combo.
So, you guys can vote from among these levels: 2-3 (Swirling Boxes), 2-4 (Bouncing Gummy), 2-A (Roped Boxes), and 8-C (Ghost Torrent). But, I could also show off Time Attack next time as well...
All right, it's boss time, Mr. Guy Man!
That works, basically returning them back to nearly how they were originally positioned, and I can use this one-way wall down here to escape.
Let's see what kind of combo I can get to begin with here...
That's it for all of the regular enemies before engaging the boss battle, so let's just gather all the coins, and then...
You have to hit them from above to press them. If you slide into them from the side like this, they won't trigger. This can be handy to know.
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points.)
Oh, that unlocked two new levels. Hmm... I think I'll just pick 2-2 to play next, since I certainly have time for a third level today.
Also, if you're up high when he deploys a slime, it'll be a ceiling slime that he sends out (which I kinda destroyed quickly there). Then, at 40% damage, he puts on the green armor again.
Brutal combo! (6 kills, 10,500 points.)
FINISH HIM!
Yeah, there was another ceiling slime, which I destroyed immediately.
80% done. Just gotta remove one more layer of armor (with 22 clicks while on the green switch), but let me finish this combo first.
Yeah, with the way that left rotating door is now, I cannot get through from the right, so I need to fix that before hitting the blue switch. This'll take some finagling.
As the level name suggests, this level has slimes that can climb walls. Still, nothing too special about them, aside from their orientations being 90° rotated from the slimes we've seen before.
...Yeah, I ran out of mana over spikes, which could've easily killed me. Fortunately, I only took two hits there, so I'm still okay.
Blaster combo! (9 kills, 22,500 points.)
Wait, this was a bad idea!
Ah, delicious green juice. Okay, now there's a detail regarding buttons that I haven't pointed out yet.
And now back to our regularly scheduled slime shooting.
Oh, these blue slimes are interesting in how they can turn corners and crawl along all sides of this landmass.
King combo! (11 kills, 32,500 points.)
Whoa, that unlocked two more levels. Alright, let's take a look at all the levels you guys can vote on now...
Alright, that's 37! Let's finish the level now!
Brutal combo! (6 kills, 10,500 points.)
Maybe I can eke out two more over here...
Hmm... Maybe I could've stretched that combo up to the red ! switch above, but I didn't want to push my luck.
So, yeah. I can force my way through the rotating doors this way, but I kinda need the blue gate switch to be pressed in order to get that gem.
